The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Ramit wins title
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: City boy Ramit Tandon won the under-13 event of the Scottish Junior Open squash championship in Edinburgh. According to information received here, Ramit crushed third-seeded Islam Khal Elfiky of Egypt 9-6, 9-6, 10-8 in the final. Ramit, in fact, had defeated all his opponents in straight games on his way to the summit clash. He surprised top seed Ian Jubb of Scotland in the quarter final and then accounted for fourth seeded Englishman Nicolas Hopcroft in the last four. Overall, India bagged three gold, two silver and two bronze in the meet. Second-seed Siddharth Suchde clinched the first ever gold for India in the under-19 event when he shocked top seed Jose Angel Becerill of Mexico 10-8, 9-4, 9-2 in the final round. The Mexican had earlier defeated another city boy Saurav Ghosal in a tight five-game thriller in the semi-final. In the girls under-19 event final, Indias top woman player Joshna Chinappa went down to Susie Pierrepont of England 4-9, 3-9, 4-9. .  Copyright 
